#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 4"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "4. Padasodhammasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on memorizing the Teaching"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.4.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.190"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa150"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācenti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six were instructing lay followers "
"to memorize the Teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"Those lay followers became disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards "
"the monks."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa151"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācessanti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six instruct lay followers to memorize "
"the Teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"those lay followers becoming disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards "
"the monks?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācetha;"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharantī”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācessatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you instruct lay followers to memorize the Teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"those lay followers becoming disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards "
"the monks?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya … "
"pe …"
msgstr ""
"This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the "
"confidence of those who have it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa152"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu anupasampannaṃ padaso dhammaṃ vāceyya pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk instructs a person who is not fully ordained to memorize the "
"Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "(<em>4</em>:<strong>53</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.4.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.4.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa153"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti "
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.191"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa154"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Anupasampanno nāma"
msgstr "A person who is not fully ordained:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā avaseso anupasampanno nāma."
msgstr "anyone except a fully ordained monk and a fully ordained nun."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa155"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Padaso nāma"
msgstr "To memorize:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "padaṃ, anupadaṃ, anvakkharaṃ, anubyañjanaṃ."
msgstr "a line, the next line, syllable by syllable, the next phrase."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa156"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Padaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A line:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "ekato paṭṭhapetvā ekato osāpenti."
msgstr "they start together and finish together."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Anupadaṃ nāma"
msgstr "The next line:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "pāṭekkaṃ paṭṭhapetvā ekato osāpenti."
msgstr "one of them starts, but they finish together."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Anvakkharaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Syllable by syllable:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "“rūpaṃ aniccan”ti vuccamāno, “run”ti opāteti."
msgstr ""
"when ‘<i lang=\"pli\">rūpaṃ aniccaṃ</i>’ is being said, he prompts him, "
"saying, ‘<i lang=\"pli\">rū</i>.’"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Anubyañjanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "The next phrase:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "“rūpaṃ aniccan”ti vuccamāno, “vedanā aniccā”ti saddaṃ nicchāreti."
msgstr ""
"when ‘<i lang=\"pli\">rūpaṃ aniccaṃ</i>,’ is being said, the other says, ‘<i "
"lang=\"pli\">vedanā aniccā</i>.’"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa157"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Yañca padaṃ, yañca anupadaṃ, yañca anvakkharaṃ, yañca anubyañjanaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"And whatever line there is, whatever next line, whatever syllable by "
"syllable, whatever next phrase—"

#. VAR: padaso → padaso dhammo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "sabbametaṃ padaso nāma."
msgstr "this is all called “to memorize the Teaching.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa158"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "Dhammo nāma"
msgstr "The Teaching:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.192"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid ""
"buddhabhāsito, sāvakabhāsito, isibhāsito, devatābhāsito, atthūpasañhito, "
"dhammūpasañhito."
msgstr ""
"what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what "
"has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected "
"with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa159"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Vāceyyāti"
msgstr "Instructs:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "padena vāceti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he instructs by the line, then for every line he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "Akkharāya vāceti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he instructs by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.4.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa160"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a person who is not fully ordained, and the monk perceives them as "
"not fully ordained, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a person who is not fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, "
"and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a person who is not fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as "
"fully ordained, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa161"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a person who is fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as not "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a person who is fully ordained, but the monk is unsure if they are, "
"he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is a person who is fully ordained, and the monk perceives them as "
"fully ordained, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.4.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa162"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "ekato uddisāpento,"
msgstr "if he causes a recitation together;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "ekato sajjhāyaṃ karonto,"
msgstr "if they practice together;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.193"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "yebhuyyena paguṇaṃ ganthaṃ bhaṇantaṃ opāteti,"
msgstr "if he prompts one who is speaking a mostly familiar text;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "osārentaṃ opāteti,"
msgstr "if he prompts one who is reciting;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa163"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc4:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "Padasodhammasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The fourth rule, the training rule on memorizing the Teaching, is finished."

